WEBVTT

00:00:01.330 --> 00:00:05.580
Yes. That guest say,
"Make me please a badge."

00:00:05.580 --> 00:00:08.370
Same as one you had.

00:00:08.370 --> 00:00:12.000
So this guy asked you
to make that badge?!

00:00:14.370 --> 00:00:16.500
What did he look like?!

00:00:16.500 --> 00:00:17.950
Look like?

00:00:17.950 --> 00:00:20.290
Hmm.

00:00:20.290 --> 00:00:21.910
Like a barrel.

00:00:21.910 --> 00:00:24.290
-A barrel?
-Barrel Titor?!

00:00:24.290 --> 00:00:25.540
Titor?

00:00:25.540 --> 00:00:27.040
No, no.

00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:29.000
Just like barrel.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:30.580
Just like barrel...?

00:00:30.580 --> 00:00:35.120
-"Barrel" in Japanese is "taru"!
-"Taru"?!

00:00:35.120 --> 00:00:38.290
I learned it from the
Rai-Net anime a while ago!

00:00:38.290 --> 00:00:40.950
There was a bad guy
called the Barrel Monster--

00:00:40.950 --> 00:00:42.290
Yes.

00:00:42.290 --> 00:00:44.080
Just "taru."

00:00:44.080 --> 00:00:45.200
...Or balloon?

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:48.580
So he's a big guy who looks
like a barrel or a balloon?

00:00:48.580 --> 00:00:50.580
How can we contact him?!

00:00:50.580 --> 00:00:51.870
Sorry.

00:00:51.870 --> 00:00:55.200
Private information. Nothing.

00:00:58.790 --> 00:01:00.950
No leads, huh...

00:01:00.950 --> 00:01:05.120
But he'll go back to pick up his
badge when it's finished, right?

00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:07.120
Apparently he left without placing an order

00:01:07.120 --> 00:01:09.580
when the guy said it'd take a week to make.

00:01:09.580 --> 00:01:11.200
Oh.

00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:14.330
Maybe it's a lost cause after all...

00:01:14.330 --> 00:01:16.500
No.

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:19.410
There's still another way.

00:01:19.410 --> 00:01:22.500
If I wait for the time leap
machine to be finished tomorrow

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:24.580
and then go back in time...

00:01:38.200 --> 00:01:43.410
suu juuoku mono kodou no kazu sae

00:01:43.410 --> 00:01:50.120
anata ni wa matataki teido no saji na toukyuu

00:01:50.120 --> 00:01:55.330
kako ni torawarete mirai o nageku mo

00:01:55.330 --> 00:02:01.250
chiri hitotsu gosan o yurusanu hitsuzen

00:02:01.250 --> 00:02:07.370
mugen ni hirogaru yume mo egaku mirai mo

00:02:07.370 --> 00:02:13.200
bokutachi ni yurusareta kyoei no kenri

00:02:13.200 --> 00:02:19.410
yuugen sore wa futatsu no hari ga shimesu

00:02:19.410 --> 00:02:24.000
zankoku na yakujou to sentaku e

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:26.290
Hacking to the Gate

00:02:26.290 --> 00:02:33.200
da kara ima ichi byou
goto ni sekaisen o koete

00:02:33.200 --> 00:02:38.120
kimi no sono egao mamoritai no sa

00:02:38.120 --> 00:02:45.120
soshite mata kanashimi
no nai jikan no ruupu e to

00:02:45.120 --> 00:02:51.790
nomi komarete yuku kodoku no kansokusha

00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:06.160
Where's Suzuha?

00:03:06.160 --> 00:03:07.750
She just left, remember?

00:03:07.750 --> 00:03:09.080
What's gotten into you?

00:03:09.080 --> 00:03:10.750
I'll explain later!

00:03:13.370 --> 00:03:15.000
Crap!

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:18.080
I forgot to ask what
time the guy showed up!

00:03:18.080 --> 00:03:20.080
Hey, how can I help you?

00:03:20.080 --> 00:03:22.000
Is that him?!

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:28.160
He does have a barrel-ish,
balloon-ish silhouette...

00:03:28.160 --> 00:03:31.290
Daru?!

00:03:31.290 --> 00:03:33.370
Ack! Okarin?!

00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:36.000
Geez...

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:38.500
Why would you make a
fake copy of the badge?!

00:03:38.500 --> 00:03:43.120
I'd feel bad if we never found
Miss Amane's old man, y'know?

00:03:43.120 --> 00:03:47.830
So I figured I could at least show
her the badge and make up a fake Titor!

00:03:47.830 --> 00:03:51.160
So you were gonna
give her false happiness?!

00:03:51.160 --> 00:03:53.330
Lies come in two types:

00:03:53.330 --> 00:03:55.750
lies that harm and lies that comfort--

00:03:55.750 --> 00:04:00.500
Do you honestly think Suzuha
would be happy if she found out?!

00:04:06.250 --> 00:04:11.660
Miss Amane told me
not to tell anyone, but...

00:04:11.660 --> 00:04:13.660
That time machine...

00:04:13.660 --> 00:04:16.700
...can only go backward in time.

00:04:17.910 --> 00:04:21.200
Once she leaves, there's no coming back.

00:04:26.700 --> 00:04:28.080
How's it going?

00:04:28.080 --> 00:04:30.250
For you.

00:04:30.250 --> 00:04:35.040
Oh! An ice-cold, no-calorie
cola is just what I needed!

00:04:35.040 --> 00:04:37.660
You're Mr. Nice Guy!

00:04:37.660 --> 00:04:40.200
Well? Do you think you can repair it?

00:04:40.200 --> 00:04:41.370
Should have it done by tomorrow.

00:04:41.370 --> 00:04:44.080
Wow! I know it's a rush job, but wow!

00:04:44.080 --> 00:04:46.450
Daru's got serious skills, all right.

00:04:46.450 --> 00:04:48.500
I told you, don't judge a book by its cover.

00:04:48.500 --> 00:04:49.370
Huh?

00:04:49.370 --> 00:04:51.700
You did?

00:04:51.700 --> 00:04:56.160
But you're right; he does seem so
unhealthy and drab on the outside!

00:04:56.160 --> 00:04:58.450
Yeah! I've changed my opinion of him!

00:04:58.450 --> 00:05:00.870
Then you can help me too, Miss Amane.

00:05:00.870 --> 00:05:04.370
And, inside the cramped time machine,
the sweltering heat will be so much

00:05:04.370 --> 00:05:06.370
that we'll forget our
embarrassment and strip our clothes...

00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:07.950
Have some self-respect, pervert!

00:05:07.950 --> 00:05:12.200
Daru-kun and Suzu-san
sure make a good match!

00:05:16.330 --> 00:05:19.410
Listen, I feel like I might never
get another chance to say this,

00:05:19.410 --> 00:05:22.120
so I'll just say it now...

00:05:22.120 --> 00:05:26.330
I'm really grateful to you all.

00:05:26.330 --> 00:05:30.910
When I first came to this time
period, I didn't know anyone,

00:05:30.910 --> 00:05:34.000
and even though this
era's so much more peaceful,

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:37.790
I found it really frightening.

00:05:37.790 --> 00:05:41.620
But now I have so many friends.

00:05:41.620 --> 00:05:44.000
I really had a lot of fun,

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.950
coming to this era and spending time with you.

00:05:48.950 --> 00:05:52.950
Even if it was for a short time,
I'm glad to have been a fellow lab member.

00:05:52.950 --> 00:05:57.290
I'm glad... I could be with you guys.

00:05:57.290 --> 00:06:01.750
Once she leaves, there's no coming back.

00:06:01.750 --> 00:06:03.200
Okabe Rintaro!

00:06:03.200 --> 00:06:06.410
-Promise you'll--
-I will change the future!

00:06:06.410 --> 00:06:11.540
I'll make it a free world, like it is now!

00:06:11.540 --> 00:06:12.830
Okabe Rintaro...?

00:06:12.830 --> 00:06:14.500
You don't...

00:06:14.500 --> 00:06:18.370
You don't regret making
memories with us, do you?

00:06:19.950 --> 00:06:22.830
If parting ways is inevitable...

00:06:22.830 --> 00:06:29.370
You don't regret being friends with
us and wish it never happened, do you?

00:06:29.370 --> 00:06:32.950
Wait, did Hashida Itaru tell you...?

00:06:32.950 --> 00:06:36.040
He's concerned about you too.

00:06:36.040 --> 00:06:38.290
I am going!

00:06:38.290 --> 00:06:41.120
Changing the future was my dad's--

00:06:41.120 --> 00:06:45.790
But don't you care what that'll mean for you?!

00:06:45.790 --> 00:06:50.620
The 70s aren't so bad either.

00:06:50.620 --> 00:06:53.580
I can make some
more friends like you guys

00:06:53.580 --> 00:06:55.750
and live a life of freedom!

00:07:03.700 --> 00:07:06.000
Here goes nothing!

00:07:10.250 --> 00:07:14.120
I think it should be okay now, but
you might wanna do one last check.

00:07:14.120 --> 00:07:15.790
Right!

00:07:18.660 --> 00:07:20.620
Yeah! It looks okay!

00:07:20.620 --> 00:07:23.580
You're really amazing!

00:07:23.580 --> 00:07:28.120
You should be happier!
You just fixed a time machine!

00:07:28.120 --> 00:07:32.250
What month and day in 1975 should I pick?!

00:07:32.250 --> 00:07:36.040
Should I go to a Capricorn day?
Or maybe an Aquarius day?

00:07:36.040 --> 00:07:37.580
No, that's for weddings!

00:07:37.580 --> 00:07:39.620
Oh, but an Aquarius day sounds good.

00:07:39.620 --> 00:07:42.750
You might make new
friends faster that way...

00:07:42.750 --> 00:07:46.000
Friends, huh?! I can't wait!

00:07:48.830 --> 00:07:52.080
"FG204"...?

00:07:52.080 --> 00:07:54.120
Say, Suzu-san!

00:07:54.120 --> 00:07:55.370
Yes?

00:07:55.370 --> 00:07:56.700
Is this...?

00:07:56.700 --> 00:08:01.790
Oh, that's the time machine's name!
My dad came up with it!

00:08:08.830 --> 00:08:11.660
M-My bicycle...?

00:08:11.660 --> 00:08:14.950
We thought it might fit
if we took the tires off!

00:08:14.950 --> 00:08:17.080
You're really fond of it, right?

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:22.000
Yeah. I'll cherish it.

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:24.540
Thank you.

00:08:24.540 --> 00:08:26.410
Aha!

00:08:26.410 --> 00:08:31.290
Mayushii knows who
your father is, Suzu-san!

00:08:32.750 --> 00:08:33.580
-What?!
-Huh?!

00:08:33.580 --> 00:08:38.700
Not only that, he's right nearby!

00:08:38.700 --> 00:08:40.870
Wh-Where?!

00:08:40.870 --> 00:08:46.450
I kept thinking they were a
good match for some reason!

00:08:46.450 --> 00:08:52.290
But now I know it's because they're family!

00:08:52.290 --> 00:08:54.250
W-Wait! You're not saying...?!

00:08:54.250 --> 00:08:57.250
Suzu-san's father...

00:08:57.250 --> 00:08:59.370
...is Daru-kun!

00:09:01.910 --> 00:09:02.870
Huh...?!

00:09:02.870 --> 00:09:05.370
That's not a funny joke!

00:09:05.370 --> 00:09:07.290
Besides, who would
ever marry this pervert--

00:09:07.290 --> 00:09:09.370
Whoa, no need to be mean!

00:09:09.370 --> 00:09:13.450
Explain! What led you to this conclusion?!

00:09:13.450 --> 00:09:16.910
First, "barrel" is "taru" in Japanese, right?

00:09:16.910 --> 00:09:19.200
Taru... Daru...

00:09:19.200 --> 00:09:20.450
Daru-kun!

00:09:20.450 --> 00:09:23.040
-Word play?!
-You call that a legitimate reason?

00:09:23.040 --> 00:09:27.250
But Suzu-san's resistance
group was founded in part

00:09:27.250 --> 00:09:30.750
by Okarin and Barrel Titor-san, right?

00:09:30.750 --> 00:09:32.750
And the only one who'd know

00:09:32.750 --> 00:09:36.290
about your independent time
machine research in Akiba in 2010

00:09:36.290 --> 00:09:38.290
and that you have the Reading Stinger--

00:09:38.290 --> 00:09:39.870
"Reading Steiner."

00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:44.370
Yeah. The only one who'd know
about that is Daru-kun, right?

00:09:45.830 --> 00:09:50.040
And the best evidence of
all that Mayushii found is...

00:09:50.910 --> 00:09:52.870
The time machine's name?

00:09:52.870 --> 00:09:54.950
FG204.

00:09:54.950 --> 00:09:57.250
It's a Future Gadget!

00:09:57.250 --> 00:09:58.620
A Future Gadget?!

00:09:58.620 --> 00:10:02.700
And see the writing next to it too?

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:10.040
Future Gadget 204, 2nd Edition, Version 2.31?!

00:10:10.040 --> 00:10:12.410
That naming style...!

00:10:21.830 --> 00:10:24.410
Dad...?

00:10:24.410 --> 00:10:27.910
A-At times like this,
you should call me "Daddy"!

00:10:27.910 --> 00:10:30.700
This is no time to act like a pervert!

00:10:37.790 --> 00:10:39.160
Dad...

00:10:39.160 --> 00:10:41.160
Y-Yeah.

00:10:41.160 --> 00:10:44.040
I came.

00:10:44.040 --> 00:10:46.830
I came to see you, Dad.

00:10:46.830 --> 00:10:50.450
In the time machine you built...

00:10:50.450 --> 00:10:52.120
Yeah...

00:10:52.120 --> 00:10:56.700
I will accomplish what you strived to do!

00:10:56.700 --> 00:10:58.870
So watch me.

00:10:58.870 --> 00:11:02.120
I-I will.

00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:04.410
I swear it.

00:11:12.410 --> 00:11:14.950
Incidentally...

00:11:14.950 --> 00:11:17.620
Was your mom cute?

00:11:17.620 --> 00:11:21.500
I'm hoping for someone short with
a baby face and humongous boobs...

00:11:24.410 --> 00:11:27.040
I think I'll keep it a secret!

00:11:29.870 --> 00:11:31.870
Well, I should probably get going.

00:11:31.870 --> 00:11:32.790
Yeah.

00:11:32.790 --> 00:11:36.410
Don't forget about us, now!

00:11:36.410 --> 00:11:37.500
Be careful.

00:11:37.500 --> 00:11:38.830
I'll be okay.

00:11:38.830 --> 00:11:42.540
I will get the IBN 5100, just you watch!

00:11:42.540 --> 00:11:45.660
And then I'll get it into your hands!

00:11:45.660 --> 00:11:49.290
So, please, change the future.

00:11:51.410 --> 00:11:54.620
I'll see you again in 35 years!

00:11:54.620 --> 00:11:57.830
I guess it'll only be a
few hours for you, though.

00:12:01.200 --> 00:12:03.000
Suzu-san!

00:12:16.290 --> 00:12:17.790
"Part-time Warrior: Thanks"
"Rukako: Summer plans"

00:12:17.790 --> 00:12:19.290
"From: Part-time Warrior"
"Subject: Thanks Goodbye"

00:12:23.790 --> 00:12:25.540
Suzuha!

00:12:25.540 --> 00:12:28.290
Let's meet again, okay?!

00:12:28.290 --> 00:12:30.580
I'll stay strong until then!

00:12:30.580 --> 00:12:33.080
So you stay strong too--!

00:12:42.330 --> 00:12:44.160
Good luck...!

00:12:47.330 --> 00:12:50.250
We've just received word that
the space satellite on the roof

00:12:50.250 --> 00:12:53.080
of the Radio Building in
Akihabara has gone missing.

00:12:53.080 --> 00:12:58.830
Hey, do you think these
were our initials on this badge?

00:12:58.830 --> 00:13:01.910
Okabe's "O," Hashida's "H," Shiina's "S"...

00:13:01.910 --> 00:13:02.950
Oh!

00:13:02.950 --> 00:13:07.040
Then the "M" is for "Makise,"
and the "A" is for "Amane"!

00:13:07.040 --> 00:13:10.330
A lab member badge!
Wanna make one ourselves?

00:13:10.330 --> 00:13:11.450
Good idea!

00:13:11.450 --> 00:13:15.000
What's wrong, Okabe?

00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:18.660
The Divergence Meter's
number hasn't changed.

00:13:18.660 --> 00:13:24.450
Maybe it'll change after the present-day
Amane-san brings us the IBN 5100?

00:13:24.450 --> 00:13:27.830
Suzuha should be 54 now, right?

00:13:27.830 --> 00:13:31.750
My own daughter's over
three decades older than me...

00:13:31.750 --> 00:13:35.500
She could be married and
have grandchildren by now!

00:13:35.500 --> 00:13:38.660
I-In other words, I could
see my own great-grandkids

00:13:38.660 --> 00:13:40.080
while I'm still so young!

00:13:40.080 --> 00:13:45.200
You'll need to spoil them like
crazy, like a good great-grandpa!

00:13:45.200 --> 00:13:46.830
It's her!

00:13:57.910 --> 00:14:00.290
Mr. Braun?!

00:14:02.750 --> 00:14:04.950
"Okabe Rintaro"

00:14:04.950 --> 00:14:06.580
A letter?

00:14:07.660 --> 00:14:10.120
Hashida Suzu...?!

00:14:10.120 --> 00:14:11.500
Could it be Suzu-san?!

00:14:11.500 --> 00:14:14.290
Seriously?! Then why is Mr. Braun...?

00:14:14.290 --> 00:14:17.750
That letter's from someone
who helped me out long ago.

00:14:17.750 --> 00:14:21.410
She asked me to give it
to you on this exact day.

00:14:21.410 --> 00:14:23.750
Where is she now?!

00:14:23.750 --> 00:14:25.540
She's dead.

00:14:26.500 --> 00:14:27.790
"Hashida Suzu"

00:14:27.790 --> 00:14:29.200
Died ten years ago.

00:14:32.830 --> 00:14:34.620
"Dear Okabe Rintaro...

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:38.000
It's been a long while. This is Amane Suzuha.

00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:41.620
For you, it's probably
only a few hours since I left.

00:14:41.620 --> 00:14:45.950
It's currently June 13, 2000.

00:14:45.950 --> 00:14:48.120
I'll get straight to the point.

00:14:48.120 --> 00:14:50.120
I failed.

00:14:51.410 --> 00:14:55.290
I failed. I failed. I failed.

00:14:55.290 --> 00:15:01.870
I failed. I failed.
I failed. I failed. I failed.

00:15:01.870 --> 00:15:07.790
I failed. I failed. I failed. I failed.

00:15:07.790 --> 00:15:13.000
I only remembered
who I am a mere year ago.

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:17.620
I had amnesia the 24 years before that.

00:15:17.620 --> 00:15:20.370
The time traveling didn't work right.

00:15:20.370 --> 00:15:23.700
The repairs were incomplete.

00:15:23.700 --> 00:15:28.700
But it wasn't your fault, Dad. It was mine!

00:15:28.700 --> 00:15:33.040
I should've just gone straight back to 1975.

00:15:33.040 --> 00:15:36.080
I should never have stopped by 2010!

00:15:36.080 --> 00:15:38.750
I shouldn't have been so selfish!

00:15:38.750 --> 00:15:42.080
The future won't change now!

00:15:42.080 --> 00:15:46.120
I couldn't get the IBN 5100.

00:15:48.540 --> 00:15:50.290
I'm sorry...

00:15:50.290 --> 00:15:52.500
I'm so sorry!

00:15:55.500 --> 00:16:00.120
Why did I even live to this age?

00:16:00.120 --> 00:16:03.950
I forgot my duty and
lived a carefree life instead!

00:16:03.950 --> 00:16:05.160
Forgive me!

00:16:05.160 --> 00:16:07.250
Forgive me! Forgive me! Forgive me!

00:16:07.250 --> 00:16:08.410
"From: Part-time Warrior"
"Subject: Sorry Goodbye"

00:16:08.410 --> 00:16:12.540
Okabe Rintaro, after that
time machine forum meeting,

00:16:12.540 --> 00:16:16.620
you stopped me
from going back to 1975.

00:16:16.620 --> 00:16:18.200
You stopped me,

00:16:18.200 --> 00:16:22.660
and the thunderstorm that
night broke the time machine.

00:16:22.660 --> 00:16:23.870
"I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
My life was"

00:16:23.870 --> 00:16:29.910
If you can turn back time, I ask
that you don't stop me that day.

00:16:31.410 --> 00:16:33.370
My life...

00:16:33.370 --> 00:16:35.370
...was a waste."

00:16:47.080 --> 00:16:48.700
Mr. Braun.

00:16:48.700 --> 00:16:52.620
What do you want?
What's with the long faces?

00:16:52.620 --> 00:16:58.120
Please, tell me how Hashida Suzu-san died.

00:16:58.120 --> 00:17:00.200
What's it to you?

00:17:00.200 --> 00:17:03.620
I need to know how she died!

00:17:03.620 --> 00:17:09.000
I need to etch it into my mind,
no matter how it happened...!

00:17:10.410 --> 00:17:14.080
Sounds like it's more
than just simple curiosity.

00:17:14.080 --> 00:17:17.750
But what kind of relationship
did you have with Suzu-san?

00:17:17.750 --> 00:17:20.370
We were... old acquaintances.

00:17:20.370 --> 00:17:22.660
Very old.

00:17:22.660 --> 00:17:28.450
But even now I remember the time
we shared together like it was yesterday!

00:17:29.080 --> 00:17:31.910
I don't really wanna talk about it, but...

00:17:31.910 --> 00:17:33.830
...it was suicide.

00:17:33.830 --> 00:17:36.500
She hanged herself in her home.

00:17:38.040 --> 00:17:43.580
She'd been mentally unstable
the year leading up to it.

00:17:47.450 --> 00:17:52.700
But she'd always been a
cheerful, kind woman before then...

00:18:03.370 --> 00:18:05.330
It's my fault...

00:18:05.330 --> 00:18:11.500
The time machine broke
because I stopped Suzuha that night...

00:18:11.500 --> 00:18:17.500
If only I hadn't sent that D-mail,
she could've safely traveled to 1975!

00:18:17.500 --> 00:18:19.160
Okarin...

00:18:20.620 --> 00:18:23.790
Hold on, Okabe! What are you doing?!

00:18:23.790 --> 00:18:27.000
At this rate, Mayuri will end up...!

00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:27.950
"To: Phone Microwave (Temporary Name)"
"Don't follow Last msg a SERN trap"

00:18:29.660 --> 00:18:33.330
You're sending a D-mail, Okarin?!

00:18:33.330 --> 00:18:36.620
It'll all disappear if you do that!

00:18:36.620 --> 00:18:38.080
I know...

00:18:38.080 --> 00:18:41.790
All the memories we made with
Suzu-san will never have happened!

00:18:41.790 --> 00:18:43.120
I know!

00:18:43.120 --> 00:18:48.580
So, please, change the future.

00:18:48.580 --> 00:18:50.450
Okarin!

00:19:00.450 --> 00:19:02.790
What do you want, Okabe?

00:19:06.580 --> 00:19:08.500
Hashida Suzu, huh...

00:19:08.500 --> 00:19:10.450
That name brings back memories.

00:19:10.450 --> 00:19:12.870
You knew her?

00:19:12.870 --> 00:19:14.250
Yes...

00:19:14.250 --> 00:19:16.700
Umm, do you know where she is now?

00:19:16.700 --> 00:19:20.120
It's been almost ten years now, I'd say...

00:19:20.120 --> 00:19:22.910
She really helped me out.

00:19:22.910 --> 00:19:26.580
I wish I could've at
least looked after her...

00:19:26.580 --> 00:19:28.870
It was a suicide, then?

00:19:28.870 --> 00:19:31.830
Huh?! A disease did her in!

00:19:31.830 --> 00:19:36.200
I live in her old house now!

00:19:39.290 --> 00:19:40.660
That bike...!

00:19:40.660 --> 00:19:45.290
Yeah. Suzu-san cherished it like crazy.

00:19:45.290 --> 00:19:49.620
I couldn't bring myself to throw it out,
so it's been sitting here for 10 years.

00:19:51.370 --> 00:19:55.580
At first, Suzu-san and
I were just regular neighbors.

00:19:55.580 --> 00:19:59.750
When I lost my house in a
fire--along with everything in it--

00:19:59.750 --> 00:20:04.540
she rented out a room here to me.

00:20:04.540 --> 00:20:07.910
Was she all alone until then?

00:20:07.910 --> 00:20:10.540
I don't think she ever married.

00:20:10.540 --> 00:20:13.750
She was an unusual woman.

00:20:13.750 --> 00:20:15.750
I once asked her why she was being so nice

00:20:15.750 --> 00:20:19.000
to a complete stranger she had no relation to.

00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:22.580
She smiled and answered with,

00:20:22.580 --> 00:20:26.910
"People's lives are a cycle
of helping and being helped.

00:20:26.910 --> 00:20:32.330
So someday you'll need to
help someone else yourself."

00:20:32.330 --> 00:20:35.290
Oh, yeah. Just a minute.

00:20:35.870 --> 00:20:38.790
This used to be Suzu-san's.

00:20:38.790 --> 00:20:42.750
Do you know what the number means?

00:20:42.750 --> 00:20:46.620
When she was sick in bed, she
always gazed at this, saying things like,

00:20:46.620 --> 00:20:52.830
"Is this number before the change
or after the change? Did I change it?"

00:20:52.830 --> 00:20:56.620
It was always on her mind to the very end.

00:21:00.290 --> 00:21:03.450
The divergence number's changed.

00:21:04.450 --> 00:21:07.700
But it's still under 1%...

00:21:07.700 --> 00:21:11.580
The train on the outer loop
line will be arriving shortly.

00:21:11.580 --> 00:21:16.370
-Please stay behind the yellow line.
-The Yamanote Line is running now?!

00:21:16.370 --> 00:21:17.870
Mayuri!

00:21:22.330 --> 00:21:23.950
Damn!

00:21:30.410 --> 00:21:32.040
Mayuri!

00:21:41.500 --> 00:21:43.410
What's with you, Okarin?

00:21:43.410 --> 00:21:46.160
Nothing.

00:21:46.160 --> 00:21:51.290
Oh, Mayushii's phone was
ringing earlier. Was that you?

00:21:51.290 --> 00:21:55.000
She was so fast asleep I couldn't wake her up.

00:22:00.700 --> 00:22:02.910
Suzuha...

00:22:02.910 --> 00:22:06.120
Has the world changed now?

00:22:06.120 --> 00:22:10.330
Has Mayuri been saved now?

00:22:20.790 --> 00:22:23.870
kisei sareta

00:22:23.870 --> 00:22:29.750
shikai mujihi naru

00:22:29.750 --> 00:22:32.700
juuni no

00:22:32.700 --> 00:22:37.500
shihai nogarerarenai

00:22:37.500 --> 00:22:41.410
ansoku no

00:22:41.410 --> 00:22:46.370
asu o negatta

00:22:46.370 --> 00:22:50.450
te no naka no

00:22:50.450 --> 00:22:55.080
toutoi jishou no chihei e

00:22:55.080 --> 00:22:59.200
torawareshi meiyaku

00:22:59.200 --> 00:23:03.620
arawareta gishou no rinkaku

00:23:03.620 --> 00:23:07.790
seimei no tenchi wa

00:23:07.790 --> 00:23:12.750
moumoku na jikan o kizanda

00:23:12.750 --> 00:23:18.120
habatake batafurai kiseki no batafurai

00:23:18.120 --> 00:23:21.620
anata e sasagu

00:23:21.620 --> 00:23:26.040
namida no batafurai mabushii batafurai

00:23:26.040 --> 00:23:28.870
subete ga

00:23:28.870 --> 00:23:33.790
ima kakikaerareru

